235461633.name: HeartGold & SoulSilver
235461633.description:
Journey to the Johto Region to Reveal HeartGold & SoulSilver! 
Pokémon are the heart and soul of any great Pokémon Trainer, and now is your chance to catch some of the greatest Pokémon of all time! With new kinds of cards that will change the way you play—like Pokémon Prime and the astonishing Pokémon LEGENDs Ho-Oh and Lugia—plus lots of Trainer cards that will accelerate your game and select Energy cards with a brand-new look, the HeartGold & SoulSilver expansion will get you started on your journey to greatness!

BasicBluePCD.name: HS: Basic Blue
BasicBluePCD.description:
Main Pokémon: Articuno, Gyarados, Lapras
Chill your opponent to the bone with this Water-type deck! Articuno can find Energy and then let loose a Freezing Wind attack. Gyarados can hit the opposing Pokémon hard and weaken every other Pokémon in play with a Berserker Splash. Lapras helps out by fetching from your deck the exact Trainer card you need! Add some awesome Trainer and Energy cards like Max Revive and Splash Energy to keep your deck strong for the long battle, and this deck displays the hidden power of the deeps!

BasicGreenPCD.name: HS: Basic Green
BasicGreenPCD.description:
Main Pokémon: Butterfree, Meganium, Torterra 
This deck has plenty of punch mixed with healing! Meganium's Giant Bloom does 60 damage for {G}{C}{C} and heals 20 damage, and Torterra's Giga Drain attack does 40 damage for {G}{C}{C} and heals the damage done. Wigglytuff has 90 HP, and when it uses Expand, it reduces damage to itself on the next turn. It may look a little softer than the HS: Basic Blue or HS: Basic Red decks, but the staying power of Grass will outlast your opponent!

BasicRedPCD.name: HS: Basic Red
BasicRedPCD.description:
Main Pokémon: Moltres, Ninetales, Arcanine
Burn it up with this Fire-type deck! Arcanine and Rapidash have big attacks that discard Energy—attach a Burning Energy so it comes right back, or use an Energy Retrieval Trainer card. Moltres is a giant Basic Pokémon that can deliver huge damage at the cost of hitting itself. And when Ninetales attacks with Flickering Flames, the hypnotic effect leaves your opponent's Pokémon Asleep. With Trainer cards like Scorched Earth and Professor Sycamore to keep your hand fired up, you can really bring on the heat!

BasicYellowPCD.name: HS: Basic Yellow
BasicYellowPCD.description:
Main Pokémon: Zapdos, Raichu, Kangaskhan
This Lightning-type deck is a rolling slugfest! Kangaskhan brings the big hits while Zapdos unleashes its Raging Thunder. Raticate can leave your opponent's Pokémon Poisoned, but they can't return the favor because it's immune to Special Conditions. With an extra-full Bench thanks to the Sky Field Stadium card, Raichu's Circle Circuit attack can hit for tons of damage! Finally, Trainer cards like Potion and Pokémon Fan Club can keep you in the game, and Double Colorless Energy can power up your Pokémon fast!

EmberSparkBundle.name: Ember Spark
EmberSparkBundle.description: The greatest fires begin with a single spark...and the Ember Spark theme deck will fan your flames of victory! Use Noctowl to add extra cards to your hand so you can build up the Energy to let Arcanine and Typhlosion use their impressive Fire Mane and Fire Spin attacks for 90 and 120 damage! By drawing and discarding at lightning speed, you'll burn through your opponent's defenses in no time!

GrowthClashBundle.name: Growth Clash
GrowthClashBundle.description: Your victories will be in full bloom when you battle using the Growth Clash theme deck! Furret helps you find the Pokémon you need, Sandslash batters the Defending Pokémon with Poison Sting, and Meganium uses Giant Bloom to both attack your opponent's Pokémon and heal itself at the same time. Can you wield the furious powers of these Pokémon to grow stronger and defeat your opponents?

HGSS1MindFloodPCD.name: Mind Flood
HGSS1MindFloodPCD.description: Let the waves wash over your opponents when you play the Mind Flood theme deck! While Hypno spends turn after turn putting your opponent's Pokémon to sleep, Exeggutor's Big Eggsplosion attack washes away your opponent's hopes of victory with the potential for tons of damage. To top it off, Feraligatr roars in with its Spinning Tail attack to flood your opponent's side of the battle with damage!
